{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878667561,"sessionID":"ses_2856236b1ffec1k4q3sY0kVI6Z","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9decc8001m7ZTt41fiAkU0o","messageID":"msg_d7a9de07f001olhopvxIo0AXZp","sessionID":"ses_2856236b1ffec1k4q3sY0kVI6Z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d4f08f61ab7a43a0a86fdd18","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-022: CLI publish 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** L  \n8: **Type:** Implementation of publish command for agent deployment to Kubernetes (AgentRuntime CR or standard Deployment/Service)\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-022.1: Publish Command CLI Interface\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `publish` Typer subcommand with options for workspace, version, image repository credentials, deployment region, cloud provider, provider type (agentcube/k8s), node port, replicas, namespace, and verbose logging.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Publish command registration\n21: - **GIVEN** the Typer app is initialized\n22: - **WHEN** the CLI loads\n23: - **THEN** the `publish` subcommand SHALL be registered as `agentcube publish`\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Default workspace resolution\n26: - **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube publish` without `-f` flag\n27: - **WHEN** the command executes\n28: - **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to current directory `\".\"`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Version specification\n31: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--version 1.2.3`\n32: - **WHEN** the command executes\n33: - **THEN** version SHALL override metadata version for publishing\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Image repository URL\n36: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--image-url registry.example.com/myimage`\n37: - **WHEN** the command executes in local build mode\n38: - **THEN** image URL SHALL be used for image push target\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Image repository credentials\n41: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--image-username` and `--image-password`\n42: - **WHEN** the command executes\n43: - **THEN** credentials SHALL be used for Docker login to image repository\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Provider selection\n46: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--provider k8s`\n47: - **WHEN** the command executes\n48: - **THEN** deployment SHALL use standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Default AgentCube provider\n51: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--provider`\n52: - **WHEN** the command executes\n53: - **THEN** provider SHALL default to `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR)\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: NodePort specification\n56: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--node-port 30080` with `--provider k8s`\n57: - **WHEN** the command executes\n58: - **THEN** Kubernetes Service SHALL use specified NodePort (30000-32767)\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Replicas specification\n61: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--replicas 3` with `--provider k8s`\n62: - **WHEN** the command executes\n63: - **THEN** Deployment SHALL be created with 3 replicas\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Namespace specification\n66: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--namespace production`\n67: - **WHEN** the command executes\n68: - **THEN** deployment SHALL target the `production` namespace\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Command-level verbose logging\n71: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--verbose` on publish command\n72: - **WHEN** the command executes\n73: - **THEN** logging level SHALL be DEBUG for publish operation only\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### REQ-022.2: PublishRuntime Integration\n78: \n79: **Requirement:** The system SHALL instantiate `PublishRuntime` with verbose flag and provider, and invoke `publish()` method with workspace path and options.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: PublishRuntime instantiation\n82: - **GIVEN** publish command is invoked\n83: - **WHEN** command handler runs\n84: - **THEN** `PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)` SHALL be instantiated\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Pass options to PublishRuntime.publish\n87: - **GIVEN** CLI options are parsed\n88: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` is called\n89: - **THEN** options dict SHALL include: `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `description`, `region`, `cloud_provider`, `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Handle PublishRuntime exceptions\n92: - **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` raises an exception\n93: - **WHEN** exception is caught\n94: - **THEN** `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` SHALL be invoked\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: Display publish success\n97: - **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n98: - **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` returns result dict\n99: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print success message with agent endpoint and status using Rich formatting\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ### REQ-022.3: AgentCube Provider Prerequisites\n104: \n105: **Requirement:** The system SHALL validate that metadata contains required URLs for AgentCube provider deployment.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Router URL requirement\n108: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube`\n109: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url`\n110: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentCube provider requires router_url in agent_metadata.yaml\")`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Workload manager URL requirement\n113: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube`\n114: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `workload_manager_url`\n115: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentCube provider requires workload_manager_url in agent_metadata.yaml\")`\n116: \n117: #### Scenario: Both URLs present\n118: - **GIVEN** metadata contains both `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n119: - **WHEN** AgentCube publish proceeds\n120: - **THEN** validation SHALL pass\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ### REQ-022.4: Image Preparation Flow\n125: \n126: **Requirement:** The system SHALL prepare the container image for publishing via Docker push (local mode) or use explicit image URL.\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Local image preparation with Docker push\n129: - **GIVEN** build mode is `local` and no `--image-url` provided\n130: - **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image()` runs\n131: - **THEN** system SHALL push image to registry using `DockerService.push_image()`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Image URL without credentials\n134: - **GIVEN** `--image-url` is provided but no credentials\n135: - **WHEN** image preparation runs\n136: - **THEN** system SHALL assume image is already pushed and use provided URL\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Image URL with credentials\n139: - **GIVEN** `--image-url`, `--image-username`, and `--image-password` are provided\n140: - **WHEN** image preparation runs\n141: - **THEN** system SHALL login, tag, and push image to specified URL\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Cloud image preparation\n144: - **GIVEN** build mode is `cloud`\n145: - **WHEN** `_prepare_cloud_image()` runs\n146: - **THEN** system SHALL use cloud provider's image registry URL\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Image tag from version\n149: - **GIVEN** metadata version is `1.2.3`\n150: - **WHEN** image is prepared\n151: - **THEN** image tag SHALL be `{agent_name}:1.2.3`\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ### REQ-022.5: AgentCube CR Deployment\n156: \n157: **Requirement:** The system SHALL deploy AgentRuntime CR using `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` when provider is `agentcube`.\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR creation\n160: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube` and prerequisites are met\n161: - **WHEN** `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` runs\n162: - **THEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` SHALL be called with agent spec\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Readiness probe configuration\n165: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port`\n166: - **WHEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n167: - **THEN** readiness probe SHALL be configured in CR spec\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Environment variable injection\n170: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `workload_manager_url` and `router_url`\n171: - **WHEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n172: - **THEN** env vars `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` SHALL be set in pod spec\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Session timeout configuration\n175: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n176: - **WHEN** CR spec is assembled\n177: - **THEN** `sessionTimeout` SHALL be set to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Image pull secret reference\n180: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n181: - **WHEN** CR spec is assembled\n182: - **THEN** `imagePullSecrets` SHALL reference `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR update\n185: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR already exists\n186: - **WHEN** publish is run again\n187: - **THEN** existing CR SHALL be patched/updated rather than recreated\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ### REQ-022.6: Standard Kubernetes Deployment\n192: \n193: **Requirement:** The system SHALL deploy standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service using `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` when provider is `k8s`.\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Kubernetes deployment creation\n196: - **GIVEN** provider is `k8s`\n197: - **WHEN** `_publish_k8s()` runs\n198: - **THEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` SHALL be called with deployment spec\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: NodePort allocation\n201: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--node-port 30080`\n202: - **WHEN** Service is created\n203: - **THEN** Service SHALL use specified NodePort\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Auto NodePort allocation\n206: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--node-port`\n207: - **WHEN** Service is created\n208: - **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL allocate ephemeral NodePort (30000-32767)\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Replica count\n211: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--replicas 3`\n212: - **WHEN** Deployment is created\n213: - **THEN** Deployment spec SHALL have `replicas: 3`\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Default replica count\n216: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--replicas`\n217: - **WHEN** Deployment is created\n218: - **THEN** Deployment SHALL have `replicas: 1`\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Deployment readiness wait\n221: - **GIVEN** Deployment is created\n222: - **WHEN** publish proceeds\n223: - **THEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120)` SHALL be called\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Deployment readiness timeout\n226: - **GIVEN** Deployment does not become ready within 120 seconds\n227: - **WHEN** wait completes\n228: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `TimeoutError(\"Deployment not ready after 120s\")`\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Service URL reporting\n231: - **GIVEN** Service is created with NodePort 30080\n232: - **WHEN** publish completes\n233: - **THEN** result SHALL include `service_url: \"http://localhost:30080\"`\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### REQ-022.7: Namespace Management\n238: \n239: **Requirement:** The system SHALL ensure target namespace exists before deployment.\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Namespace creation\n242: - **GIVEN** target namespace does not exist\n243: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` runs\n244: - **THEN** namespace SHALL be created via Kubernetes API\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: Namespace already exists\n247: - **GIVEN** target namespace exists\n248: - **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` runs\n249: - **THEN** no-op SHALL occur\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Default namespace\n252: - **GIVEN** user does not specify `--namespace`\n253: - **WHEN** deployment proceeds\n254: - **THEN** namespace SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ### REQ-022.8: Publish Metadata Update\n259: \n260: **Requirement:** The system SHALL update workspace metadata with deployment information after successful publish.\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: Agent ID assignment\n263: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created successfully\n264: - **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata()` runs\n265: - **THEN** metadata `agent_id` SHALL be set to CR name\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Agent endpoint recording\n268: - **GIVEN** deployment completes with service URL\n269: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n270: - **THEN** metadata `agent_endpoint` SHALL be set to service URL\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: Session ID generation\n273: - **GIVEN** publish completes\n274: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n275: - **THEN** metadata `session_id` SHALL be generated or preserved\n276: \n277: #### Scenario: Deployment info recording\n278: - **GIVEN** k8s provider deployment completes\n279: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n280: - **THEN** metadata `k8s_deployment` SHALL include deployment name, service name, namespace, node_port\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: Metadata persistence\n283: - **GIVEN** metadata updates are made\n284: - **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata()` completes\n285: - **THEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` SHALL be written with `yaml.dump(exclude_none=True)`\n286: \n287: ---\n288: \n289: ### REQ-022.9: Publish Status Reporting\n290: \n291: **Requirement:** The system SHALL report publish results with deployment status, agent endpoint, and next steps.\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: Publish success output\n294: - **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n295: - **WHEN** result is returned\n296: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print:\n297:   ```\n298:   ✓ Publish completed successfully\n299:   Agent: {agent_name}\n300:   Provider: {provider}\n301:   Endpoint: {agent_endpoint}\n302:   Status: {status}\n303:   ```\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider success\n306: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is deployed\n307: - **WHEN** publish completes\n308: - **THEN** output SHALL include CR name and namespace\n309: \n310: #### Scenario: K8s provider success\n311: - **GIVEN** Deployment + Service are deployed\n312: - **WHEN** publish completes\n313: - **THEN** output SHALL include service URL and node port\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Next step guidance\n316: - **GIVEN** publish succeeds\n317: - **WHEN** output is printed\n318: - **THEN** CLI SHALL suggest next command: `agentcube invoke` with appropriate flags\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ### REQ-022.10: Error Handling\n323: \n324: **Requirement:** The system SHALL handle publish failures with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n325: \n326: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisite failure\n327: - **GIVEN** metadata lacks router_url\n328: - **WHEN** publish validation runs\n329: - **THEN** system SHALL print error in red and exit with code 1\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: Image push failure\n332: - **GIVEN** Docker push fails (auth error, network error)\n333: - **WHEN** image preparation runs\n334: - **THEN** error SHALL be reported and exit code 1 returned\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API failure\n337: - **GIVEN** Kubernetes API is unreachable\n338: - **WHEN** deployment is attempted\n339: - **THEN** error SHALL be reported and exit code 1 returned\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Deployment readiness failure\n342: - **GIVEN** Deployment fails to become ready\n343: - **WHEN** wait timeout expires\n344: - **THEN** error SHALL include pod events and exit code 1\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: CRD not installed\n347: - **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube` but CRD not installed\n348: - **WHEN** CR creation is attempted\n349: - **THEN** error SHALL indicate CRD is missing and exit with code 1\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ## Data Types\n354: \n355: ```python\n356: # Publish command options\n357: class PublishOptions(TypedDict, total=False):\n358:     workspace: str\n359:     version: Optional[str]\n360:     image_url: Optional[str]\n361:     image_username: Optional[str]\n362:     image_password: Optional[str]\n363:     description: Optional[str]\n364:     region: Optional[str]\n365:     cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n366:     provider: str  # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\"\n367:     node_port: Optional[int]\n368:     replicas: Optional[int]\n369:     namespace: Optional[str]\n370:     verbose: bool\n371: \n372: # Publish result structure\n373: class PublishResult(TypedDict):\n374:     agent_name: str\n375:     provider: str\n376:     agent_id: Optional[str]\n377:     agent_endpoint: str\n378:     status: str\n379:     deployment_info: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]\n380:     publish_time: str\n381: ```\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## CLI Flags Summary\n386: \n387: | Flag | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n388: |------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n389: | `--workspace` | `-f` | str | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace |\n390: | `--version` | - | Optional[str] | None | Semantic version string |\n391: | `--image-url` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository URL |\n392: | `--image-username` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository username |\n393: | `--image-password` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository password |\n394: | `--description` | - | Optional[str] | None | Agent description |\n395: | `--region` | - | Optional[str] | None | Deployment region |\n396: | `--cloud-provider` | - | Optional[str] | None | Cloud provider name |\n397: | `--provider` | - | str | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: agentcube or k8s |\n398: | `--node-port` | - | Optional[int] | None | NodePort for k8s Service |\n399: | `--replicas` | - | Optional[int] | None | Replicas for k8s Deployment |\n400: | `--namespace` | - | Optional[str] | None | Kubernetes namespace |\n401: | `--verbose` | - | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n402: \n403: ---\n404: \n405: ## Environment Variables\n406: \n407: | Variable | Description | Default |\n408: |----------|-------------|---------|\n409: | `KUBECONFIG` | Kubernetes config file | `~/.kube/config` |\n410: | `ROUTER_URL` | AgentCube router URL | - |\n411: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | AgentCube workload manager URL | - |\n412: | `DOCKER_HOST` | Docker daemon socket | system default |\n413: \n414: ---\n415: \n416: ## Error Codes\n417: \n418: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n419: |-------|-----------|---------|\n420: | Missing router_url | 1 | \"AgentCube provider requires router_url in agent_metadata.yaml\" |\n421: | Missing workload_manager_url | 1 | \"AgentCube provider requires workload_manager_url in agent_metadata.yaml\" |\n422: | Image push failure | 1 | \"Failed to push image: {detail}\" |\n423: | Kubernetes API failure | 1 | \"Kubernetes API error: {detail}\" |\n424: | Deployment timeout | 1 | \"Deployment not ready after {timeout}s\" |\n425: | CRD not installed | 1 | \"AgentRuntime CRD not installed. Run: kubectl apply -f ...\" |\n426: | Invalid node-port | 1 | \"NodePort must be between 30000-32767\" |\n427: | Namespace creation failure | 1 | \"Failed to create namespace: {detail}\" |\n428: \n429: ---\n430: \n431: ## Dependencies\n432: \n433: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n434: |---------|---------|---------|\n435: | `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework |\n436: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Data validation |\n437: | `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK |\n438: | `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Output formatting |\n439: | `kubernetes` | >=28.0.0 | Kubernetes client |\n440: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | Metadata handling |\n441: | `httpx` | >=0.24.0 | HTTP client |\n442: \n443: ---\n444: \n445: ## Acceptance Checklist\n446: \n447: - [ ] `agentcube/cli/main.py` — publish command registered with Typer\n448: - [ ] `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` — PublishRuntime class implemented\n449: - [ ] `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` — AgentCubeProvider for CR deployment\n450: - [ ] `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` — KubernetesProvider for standard deployment\n451: - [ ] `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` — DockerService for image push\n452: - [ ] Image preparation flow (local push, cloud, explicit URL)\n453: - [ ] AgentCube CR deployment with readiness probe\n454: - [ ] K8s Deployment + NodePort Service deployment\n455: - [ ] Namespace management\n456: - [ ] Metadata update with deployment info\n457: - [ ] Success/failure output with Rich formatting\n458: - [ ] Verbose mode streams deployment logs\n459: - [ ] Error handling with appropriate exit codes\n460: - [ ] Next step guidance after successful publish\n461: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for publish path\n462: \n463: ---\n464: \n465: ## Open Questions\n466: \n467: 1. Should publish command support `--dry-run` for validation without deployment?\n468: 2. Should `--wait` flag be added to control readiness wait behavior?\n469: 3. Should publish support `--rollback` on deployment failure?\n470: 4. Should multi-region deployment be supported via `--region` flag?\n\n(End of file - total 470 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-022: CLI publish 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L  \n**Type:** Implementation of publish command for agent deployment to Kubernetes (AgentRuntime CR or standard Deployment/Service)\n\n**Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-022.1: Publish Command CLI Interface\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `publish` Typer subcommand with options for workspace, version, image repository credentials, deployment region, cloud provider, provider type (agentcube/k8s), node port, replicas, namespace, and verbose logging.\n\n#### Scenario: Publish command registration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775878667509,"end":1775878667558}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878667563,"sessionID":"ses_2856236b1ffec1k4q3sY0kVI6Z","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9df1d1001V2engIyGAi1Sqx","messageID":"msg_d7a9de07f001olhopvxIo0AXZp","sessionID":"ses_2856236b1ffec1k4q3sY0kVI6Z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f3c7ad593733407cb8740ec0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_029.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_029.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 实现 AgentCube Python SDK 的底层 HTTP 客户端模块，提供与控制平面（Workload Manager）和数据平面（Router）的通信能力。该模块是 SDK 的核心基础设施，支撑 `CodeInterpreterClient` 和 `AgentRuntimeClient` 的全部网络交互。\n6: \n7: ## Scope\n8: \n9: ### 包含内容\n10: \n11: 1. **控制平面客户端** (`ControlPlaneClient`)\n12:    - Session 创建/删除\n13:    - Workload Manager URL 和认证令牌解析\n14:    - 连接池管理（`pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`）\n15: \n16: 2. **数据平面客户端**\n17:    - `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`: 代码执行、文件操作\n18:    - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: Agent Runtime 调用\n19:    - Router URL 路径构建（`urljoin` 相对路径拼接）\n20:    - Session ID 头管理（`x-agentcube-session-id`）\n21: \n22: 3. **工具模块**\n23:    - `create_session()`: 创建带连接池的 `requests.Session`\n24:    - `read_token_from_file()`: 读取 Kubernetes SA Token\n25:    - `get_logger()`: 统一日志配置\n26: \n27: 4. **异常层次结构**\n28:    - `AgentCubeError` (基类)\n29:    - `CommandExecutionError` (命令非零退出)\n30:    - `SessionError` / `DataPlaneError` (预留扩展)\n31: \n32: 5. **配置解析**\n33:    - 环境变量：`ROUTER_URL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n34:    - 参数优先级：显式参数 > 环境变量 > 默认值\n35: \n36: ### 不包含内容\n37: \n38: - 高层客户端（`CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient`）的业务逻辑封装\n39: - JWT Token 生成（由 Router 处理）\n40: - 服务端代码\n41: \n42: ## Impact Analysis\n43: \n44: ### 依赖影响\n45: \n46: | 依赖项 | 版本 | 用途 |\n47: |--------|------|------|\n48: | `requests` | latest | HTTP 客户端 |\n49: | `PyJWT` | >=2.0.0 | 预留 JWT 支持 |\n50: | `cryptography` | latest | 加密支持 |\n51: \n52: ### 模块依赖关系\n53: \n54: ```\n55: agentcube/\n56: ├── __init__.py              # 导出 CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n57: ├── code_interpreter.py      # 依赖 ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n58: ├── agent_runtime.py         # 依赖 AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n59: ├── clients/\n60: │   ├── control_plane.py     # 依赖 create_session, read_token_from_file\n61: │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # 依赖 create_session\n62: │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # 依赖 create_session\n63: ├── utils/\n64: │   ├── http.py              # create_session\n65: │   ├── utils.py             # read_token_from_file\n66: │   └── log.py               # get_logger\n67: └── exceptions.py            # 异常层次结构\n68: ```\n69: \n70: ### 向后兼容性\n71: \n72: - 首次实现，无破坏性变更风险\n73: - 预留 `SessionError` / `DataPlaneError` 供未来扩展\n74: \n75: ### 测试影响\n76: \n77: - 需覆盖 HTTP 超时、连接池复用、异常场景\n78: - Mock 服务端响应测试客户端行为（404 处理、Token 缺失等）\n79: \n80: ## Alternatives Considered\n81: \n82: ### 方案 1: 使用 `httpx` 替代 `requests`\n83: \n84: **优点:**\n85: - 原生异步支持\n86: - 更现代的 API 设计\n87: \n88: **缺点:**\n89: - 增加学习曲线\n90: - 与现有 AgentCube 技术栈不一致\n91: \n92: **决策:** 选择 `requests`，保持技术栈统一，降低维护成本。\n93: \n94: ### 方案 2: 集中式配置类\n95: \n96: **优点:**\n97: - 配置统一管理\n98: - 便于序列化/反序列化\n99: \n100: **缺点:**\n101: - 增加 API 复杂度\n102: - 与现有分布式配置解析模式不一致\n103: \n104: **决策:** 采用分布式配置解析（各客户端自行处理参数和环境变量），保持与 spec 一致。\n105: \n106: ### 方案 3: 同步/异步双版本客户端\n107: \n108: **优点:**\n109: - 同时支持同步和异步场景\n110: \n111: **缺点:**\n112: - 代码复杂度翻倍\n113: - 增加维护负担\n114: \n115: **决策:** 首期仅实现同步版本，异步支持待后续需求明确后添加。\n116: \n117: ## Implementation Notes\n118: \n119: ### 关键实现细节\n120: \n121: 1. **超时处理**: `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)` 元组形式，控制平面和数据平面默认 `connect_timeout=5.0`, `read_timeout=120`\n122: \n123: 2. **Session ID 管理**: \n124:    - 控制平面：`create_session()` 返回 session_id\n125:    - 数据平面：通过 `x-agentcube-session-id` 头传递\n126: \n127: 3. **文件上传**: multipart/form-data 格式，需单独设置 `x-agentcube-session-id` 头\n128: \n129: 4. **错误处理**: \n130:    - 控制平面 404 视为成功（`delete_session`）\n131:    - 命令非零退出抛出 `CommandExecutionError`\n132: \n133: ## Success Criteria\n134: \n135: - [ ] 所有 HTTP 端点符合 spec 定义的路径和参数\n136: - [ ] 连接池正确配置（10/10）\n137: - [ ] 超时行为符合预期（默认 120s + 2s buffer）\n138: - [ ] 异常层次结构完整\n139: - [ ] 环境变量解析正确\n140: - [ ] 单元测试覆盖所有场景\n\n(End of file - total 140 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## Purpose\n\n实现 AgentCube Python SDK 的底层 HTTP 客户端模块，提供与控制平面（Workload Manager）和数据平面（Router）的通信能力。该模块是 SDK 的核心基础设施，支撑 `CodeInterpreterClient` 和 `AgentRuntimeClient` 的全部网络交互。\n\n## Scope\n\n### 包含内容\n\n1. **控制平面客户端** (`ControlPlaneClient`)\n   - Session 创建/删除\n   - Workload Manager URL 和认证令牌解析\n   - 连接池管理（`pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`）\n\n2. **数据平面客户端**\n   - `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`: 代码执行、文件操作\n   - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: Agent Runtime 调用\n   - Router URL 路径构建（`urljoin` 相对路径拼接）\n   - Session ID 头管理（`x-agentcube-session-id`）","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_029.md","time":{"start":1775878667513,"end":1775878667562}}}}
