{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878674228,"sessionID":"ses_2856236b1ffec1k4q3sY0kVI6Z","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9e1290001uDPaIK3H4aGily","messageID":"msg_d7a9dfd67001Rj7OZ6ozSBw1QO","sessionID":"ses_2856236b1ffec1k4q3sY0kVI6Z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b355b1bd1b434262b74ff292","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-021: CLI build 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Implementation of build command for container image building\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-021.1: Build Command CLI Interface\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `build` Typer subcommand with options for workspace path, proxy configuration, cloud provider selection, output path, and verbose logging.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Build command registration\n21: - **GIVEN** the Typer app is initialized\n22: - **WHEN** the CLI loads\n23: - **THEN** the `build` subcommand SHALL be registered as `agentcube build`\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Default workspace resolution\n26: - **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube build` without `-f` flag\n27: - **WHEN** the command executes\n28: - **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to current directory `\".\"`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Custom workspace path\n31: - **GIVEN** user specifies `-f /path/to/workspace`\n32: - **WHEN** the command executes\n33: - **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to the provided absolute or relative path\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Proxy configuration via flag\n36: - **GIVEN** user specifies `-p http://proxy:port` or `--proxy http://proxy:port`\n37: - **WHEN** the command executes\n38: - **THEN** proxy SHALL be passed to build options for dependency resolution\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Cloud provider selection\n41: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--cloud-provider huawei`\n42: - **WHEN** the command executes\n43: - **THEN** cloud provider SHALL override default build mode to `cloud`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Output path for build artifacts\n46: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--output /path/to/output`\n47: - **WHEN** the command completes\n48: - **THEN** build artifacts SHALL be copied or linked to the output path\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Command-level verbose logging\n51: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--verbose` on build command\n52: - **WHEN** the command executes\n53: - **THEN** logging level SHALL be DEBUG for build operation only\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### REQ-021.2: BuildRuntime Integration\n58: \n59: **Requirement:** The system SHALL instantiate `BuildRuntime` with verbose flag and invoke `build()` method with workspace path and options.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: BuildRuntime instantiation\n62: - **GIVEN** build command is invoked\n63: - **WHEN** command handler runs\n64: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)` SHALL be instantiated\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Pass options to BuildRuntime.build\n67: - **GIVEN** CLI options are parsed\n68: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` is called\n69: - **THEN** options dict SHALL include: `proxy`, `cloud_provider`, `output`, and any metadata overrides\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Handle BuildRuntime exceptions\n72: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` raises an exception\n73: - **WHEN** exception is caught\n74: - **THEN** `_handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)` SHALL be invoked\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Display build success\n77: - **GIVEN** build completes successfully\n78: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` returns result dict\n79: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print success message with image name, tag, and build time using Rich formatting\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### REQ-021.3: Build Mode Resolution\n84: \n85: **Requirement:** The system SHALL determine build mode (local vs cloud) from metadata, with CLI `--cloud-provider` flag taking precedence.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Default to local build\n88: - **GIVEN** metadata has `build_mode: local` or no build_mode specified\n89: - **WHEN** `--cloud-provider` is not provided\n90: - **THEN** build mode SHALL be `local`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Cloud provider overrides to cloud mode\n93: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--cloud-provider huawei`\n94: - **WHEN** build mode is resolved\n95: - **THEN** build mode SHALL be `cloud` regardless of metadata\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Cloud mode requires cloud provider\n98: - **GIVEN** metadata has `build_mode: cloud`\n99: - **WHEN** no `--cloud-provider` is specified\n100: - **THEN** system SHALL raise error requiring cloud provider name\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### REQ-021.4: Local Docker Build Flow\n105: \n106: **Requirement:** The system SHALL execute local Docker build using `DockerService` when build mode is `local`.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Docker availability check\n109: - **GIVEN** build mode is `local`\n110: - **WHEN** build starts\n111: - **THEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` SHALL be called first\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Docker not available error\n114: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running\n115: - **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` fails\n116: - **THEN** `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` SHALL be raised\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Build image with DockerService\n119: - **GIVEN** Docker is available\n120: - **WHEN** local build proceeds\n121: - **THEN** `DockerService.build_image()` SHALL be called with:\n122:   - `dockerfile_path`: workspace/Dockerfile\n123:   - `context_path`: workspace\n124:   - `image_name`: `{agent_name}`\n125:   - `tag`: `{version}` or `latest`\n126:   - `build_args`: proxy settings if provided\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Image tagging convention\n129: - **GIVEN** metadata version is `1.2.3`\n130: - **WHEN** image is built\n131: - **THEN** image tag SHALL be `{agent_name}:1.2.3`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Fallback tag when no version\n134: - **GIVEN** metadata has no version\n135: - **WHEN** image is built\n136: - **THEN** image tag SHALL default to `{agent_name}:latest`\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ### REQ-021.5: Version Increment Logic\n141: \n142: **Requirement:** The system SHALL increment version before local build and revert on failure.\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Patch version increment\n145: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.2.3`\n146: - **WHEN** build starts\n147: - **THEN** version SHALL become `1.2.4` before build\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Minor version increment\n150: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.2.0` and user requests minor bump\n151: - **WHEN** build starts\n152: - **THEN** version SHALL become `1.3.0`\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Major version increment\n155: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.0.0` and user requests major bump\n156: - **WHEN** build starts\n157: - **THEN** version SHALL become `2.0.0`\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Pre-release version handling\n160: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.0.0-alpha.1`\n161: - **WHEN** build starts\n162: - **THEN** version SHALL increment pre-release to `1.0.0-alpha.2`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Version revert on build failure\n165: - **GIVEN** build fails after version increment\n166: - **WHEN** error is caught\n167: - **THEN** metadata version SHALL be reverted to original value\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Version string fallback\n170: - **GIVEN** version is not semver format (e.g., `v1.0`)\n171: - **WHEN** increment is attempted\n172: - **THEN** system SHALL append `.1` (e.g., `v1.0.1`) or use `{version}-1` fallback\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ### REQ-021.6: Cloud Build Flow\n177: \n178: **Requirement:** The system SHALL trigger cloud build when build mode is `cloud` and cloud provider is specified.\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Cloud build prerequisite validation\n181: - **GIVEN** build mode is `cloud`\n182: - **WHEN** build starts\n183: - **THEN** system SHALL validate cloud provider credentials/configuration\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Huawei cloud provider\n186: - **GIVEN** `--cloud-provider huawei`\n187: - **WHEN** cloud build is triggered\n188: - **THEN** system SHALL use Huawei Cloud Container Registry API\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Cloud provider not supported\n191: - **GIVEN** `--cloud-provider unknown-provider`\n192: - **WHEN** build starts\n193: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Unsupported cloud provider: unknown-provider\")`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Cloud build status polling\n196: - **GIVEN** cloud build is triggered\n197: - **WHEN** build is in progress\n198: - **THEN** system SHALL poll build status with progress indicator\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Cloud build timeout\n201: - **GIVEN** cloud build exceeds timeout (default 600s)\n202: - **WHEN** polling continues\n203: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `TimeoutError(\"Cloud build exceeded timeout\")`\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ### REQ-021.7: Build Validation Prerequisites\n208: \n209: **Requirement:** The system SHALL validate workspace prerequisites before build.\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Dockerfile existence check\n212: - **GIVEN** build is about to start\n213: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()` runs\n214: - **THEN** system SHALL check for Dockerfile in workspace\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Missing Dockerfile\n217: - **GIVEN** no Dockerfile exists in workspace\n218: - **WHEN** validation runs\n219: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace\")`\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Metadata validation\n222: - **GIVEN** build is about to start\n223: - **WHEN** prerequisites are validated\n224: - **THEN** system SHALL verify `agent_metadata.yaml` exists and is valid\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: Image name validation\n227: - **GIVEN** agent_name contains invalid characters\n228: - **WHEN** build starts\n229: - **THEN** system SHALL sanitize or reject invalid image names per Docker naming rules\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ### REQ-021.8: Build Output and Reporting\n234: \n235: **Requirement:** The system SHALL report build results with image details, build time, and next steps.\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Build success output\n238: - **GIVEN** build completes successfully\n239: - **WHEN** result is returned\n240: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print:\n241:   ```\n242:   ✓ Build completed successfully\n243:   Image: {image_name}:{tag}\n244:   Image ID: {image_id}\n245:   Size: {image_size}\n246:   Build time: {build_time}s\n247:   ```\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Build result metadata update\n250: - **GIVEN** build succeeds\n251: - **WHEN** `_update_build_metadata()` runs\n252: - **THEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` SHALL be updated with image info (name, tag, id, size)\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Verbose build logs\n255: - **GIVEN** `--verbose` is true\n256: - **WHEN** build runs\n257: - **THEN** Docker build logs SHALL be streamed to console\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: Next step guidance\n260: - **GIVEN** build succeeds\n261: - **WHEN** output is printed\n262: - **THEN** CLI SHALL suggest next command: `agentcube publish` with appropriate flags\n263: \n264: ---\n265: \n266: ### REQ-021.9: Proxy Configuration\n267: \n268: **Requirement:** The system SHALL support proxy configuration for dependency resolution during build.\n269: \n270: #### Scenario: Proxy via CLI flag\n271: - **GIVEN** user specifies `-p http://proxy:port`\n272: - **WHEN** build runs\n273: - **THEN** proxy SHALL be set as `build_arg` for Docker build\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: Proxy environment variable fallback\n276: - **GIVEN** no `-p` flag but `HTTP_PROXY` env var is set\n277: - **WHEN** build runs\n278: - **THEN** proxy SHALL be read from environment\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Proxy for pip installs\n281: - **GIVEN** Python workspace with requirements.txt\n282: - **WHEN** build processes dependencies\n283: - **THEN** pip install SHALL use `--proxy` flag if proxy is configured\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Proxy for maven builds\n286: - **GIVEN** Java workspace with pom.xml\n287: - **WHEN** build processes dependencies\n288: - **THEN** maven settings.xml SHALL include proxy configuration\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ## Data Types\n293: \n294: ```python\n295: # Build command options\n296: class BuildOptions(TypedDict, total=False):\n297:     workspace: str\n298:     proxy: Optional[str]\n299:     cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n300:     output: Optional[str]\n301:     verbose: bool\n302: \n303: # Build result structure\n304: class BuildResult(TypedDict):\n305:     image_name: str\n306:     image_tag: str\n307:     image_id: str\n308:     image_size: str\n309:     build_time: str\n310:     build_mode: str\n311:     cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n312: ```\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## CLI Flags Summary\n317: \n318: | Flag | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n319: |------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n320: | `--workspace` | `-f` | str | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace |\n321: | `--proxy` | `-p` | Optional[str] | None | Proxy URL for dependencies |\n322: | `--cloud-provider` | - | Optional[str] | None | Cloud provider name (huawei, etc.) |\n323: | `--output` | - | Optional[str] | None | Output path for artifacts |\n324: | `--verbose` | - | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ## Environment Variables\n329: \n330: | Variable | Description | Default |\n331: |----------|-------------|---------|\n332: | `HTTP_PROXY` | HTTP proxy for builds | - |\n333: | `HTTPS_PROXY` | HTTPS proxy for builds | - |\n334: | `DOCKER_HOST` | Docker daemon socket | system default |\n335: \n336: ---\n337: \n338: ## Error Codes\n339: \n340: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n341: |-------|-----------|---------|\n342: | Docker unavailable | 1 | \"Docker is not available or not running\" |\n343: | Missing Dockerfile | 1 | \"Dockerfile not found in workspace\" |\n344: | Invalid cloud provider | 1 | \"Unsupported cloud provider: {name}\" |\n345: | Build failure | 1 | \"Build failed: {detail}\" |\n346: | Cloud build timeout | 1 | \"Cloud build exceeded timeout ({duration}s)\" |\n347: | Version increment failure | 1 | \"Failed to increment version: {detail}\" |\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ## Dependencies\n352: \n353: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n354: |---------|---------|---------|\n355: | `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework |\n356: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Data validation |\n357: | `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK |\n358: | `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Output formatting |\n359: | `semver` | >=3.0.0 | Version parsing |\n360: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | Metadata handling |\n361: \n362: ---\n363: \n364: ## Acceptance Checklist\n365: \n366: - [ ] `agentcube/cli/main.py` — build command registered with Typer\n367: - [ ] `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` — BuildRuntime class implemented\n368: - [ ] `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` — DockerService for local builds\n369: - [ ] `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/` — Cloud provider implementations\n370: - [ ] Version increment logic with rollback on failure\n371: - [ ] Proxy configuration via flag and environment\n372: - [ ] Build prerequisites validation (Dockerfile, metadata)\n373: - [ ] Success/failure output with Rich formatting\n374: - [ ] Verbose mode streams build logs\n375: - [ ] Error handling with appropriate exit codes\n376: - [ ] Next step guidance after successful build\n377: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for build path\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Open Questions\n382: \n383: 1. Should build command support `--tag` override for custom image tags?\n384: 2. Should multi-platform builds (`--platform`) be supported in initial release?\n385: 3. Should build cache options (`--no-cache`, `--cache-from`) be exposed?\n\n(End of file - total 385 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-021: CLI build 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Implementation of build command for container image building\n\n**Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-021.1: Build Command CLI Interface\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `build` Typer subcommand with options for workspace path, proxy configuration, cloud provider selection, output path, and verbose logging.\n\n#### Scenario: Build command registration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md","time":{"start":1775878674203,"end":1775878674225}}}}
