{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878846584,"sessionID":"ses_2856236b1ffec1k4q3sY0kVI6Z","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9e6a0b001LAvg5tDU273KqK","messageID":"msg_d7a9e5a3b001sl32K3eWAu27wV","sessionID":"ses_2856236b1ffec1k4q3sY0kVI6Z","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_784e5e4aa30a47b4a8ad25da","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification — AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L  \n**Type:** Helm Chart implementation for AgentCube control plane components\n\n**Base Specs:** deployment/spec.md, deployment/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-030.1: Chart.yaml Metadata\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Chart.yaml with apiVersion v1, name agentcube, version 0.1.0, and appVersion 1.0.0.\n\n#### Scenario: Chart.yaml structure\n- **GIVEN** the Helm chart is initialized\n- **WHEN** Chart.yaml is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n  - `apiVersion: v1`\n  - `name: agentcube`\n  - `description: A Helm chart for AgentCube`\n  - `version: 0.1.0`\n  - `appVersion: \"1.0.0\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Chart metadata keywords\n- **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** metadata is defined\n- **THEN** keywords SHALL include: `agent`, `sandbox`, `kubernetes`, `volcano`\n\n#### Scenario: Chart maintainers\n- **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** maintainers are defined\n- **THEN** maintainers SHALL include Volcano Authors with email `volcano-sh@googlegroups.com`\n\n#### Scenario: Chart home and sources\n- **GIVEN** Chart.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** home and sources are defined\n- **THEN** they SHALL reference `https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-030.2: values.yaml Configuration Tree\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement values.yaml with complete configuration tree for Redis, Router, WorkloadManager, and Volcano Scheduler.\n\n#### Scenario: Redis configuration\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** redis configuration is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `redis.addr: \"\"` (empty default, user must provide)\n  - `redis.password: \"\"` (empty default for non-auth Redis)\n\n#### Scenario: Router replicas and image\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** router configuration is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `router.replicas: 1`\n  - `router.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router`\n  - `router.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n  - `router.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Router service configuration\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** router service is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `router.service.type: ClusterIP`\n  - `router.service.port: 8080`\n  - `router.service.targetPort: 8080`\n\n#### Scenario: Router resources\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** router resources are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `router.resources.limits.cpu: 500m`\n  - `router.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi`\n  - `router.resources.requests.cpu: 100m`\n  - `router.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi`\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC toggle\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** router.rbac configuration is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `router.rbac.create: false` (disabled by default)\n  - `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` (empty for auto-generated or default)\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager replicas and image\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** workloadmanager configuration is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `workloadmanager.replicas: 1`\n  - `workloadmanager.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager`\n  - `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n  - `workloadmanager.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager service configuration\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** workloadmanager service is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `workloadmanager.service.type: ClusterIP`\n  - `workloadmanager.service.port: 8080`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager resources\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** workloadmanager resources are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: 500m`\n  - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi`\n  - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu: 100m`\n  - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi`\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager extraEnv\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** workloadmanager.extraEnv is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` for additional environment variables\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler enabled toggle\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** volcano.scheduler configuration is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (disabled by default)\n  - `volcano.scheduler.replicas: 1`\n  - `volcano.scheduler.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler`\n  - `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n  - `volcano.scheduler.image.tag: \"latest\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Image pull secrets\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** imagePullSecrets is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` by default\n\n#### Scenario: Name overrides\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** nameOverride and fullnameOverride are defined\n- **THEN** they SHALL be empty strings `\"\"` by default\n\n#### Scenario: Router extraEnv\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** router.extraEnv is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL be an empty list `[]` for additional environment variables\n\n#### Scenario: Router config\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml is created\n- **WHEN** router.config is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL be an empty object `{}` for additional container configuration\n\n---\n\n### REQ-030.3: Workload Manager Deployment Template\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Workload Manager Deployment template with correct environment variables, probes, and resource configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager Deployment metadata\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** Workload Manager Deployment is created\n- **THEN** metadata SHALL include:\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager replicas from values\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.replicas: 2`\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `2`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager image from values\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has custom image repository\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** container image SHALL be `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager environment variables\n- **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **WHEN** container env is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from fieldRef `metadata.namespace`\n  - `REDIS_ADDR` from `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}`\n  - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from Secret `{{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager extraEnv injection\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.extraEnv` entries\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** extraEnv entries SHALL be injected into container env\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager args\n- **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **WHEN** container args are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `--port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n  - `--runtime-class-name=` (empty)\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager liveness probe\n- **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **WHEN** livenessProbe is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `httpGet.path: /health`\n  - `httpGet.port: http`\n  - `initialDelaySeconds: 10`\n  - `periodSeconds: 10`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager readiness probe\n- **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **WHEN** readinessProbe is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `httpGet.path: /health`\n  - `httpGet.port: http`\n  - `initialDelaySeconds: 5`\n  - `periodSeconds: 5`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager resources from values\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `workloadmanager.resources` defined\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** `resources` SHALL be rendered from values using `toYaml`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager image pull secrets\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `imagePullSecrets` entries\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** `imagePullSecrets` SHALL be injected into pod spec\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager service account\n- **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **WHEN** serviceAccountName is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL be `workloadmanager`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager Service\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** Workload Manager Service is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - `type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}`\n  - `port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n  - `targetPort: http`\n  - Selector: `app: workloadmanager`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-030.4: Router Deployment Template\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Router Deployment template with correct environment variables, probes, and WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL.\n\n#### Scenario: Router Deployment metadata\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** Router Deployment is created\n- **THEN** metadata SHALL include:\n  - `name: agentcube-router`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: agentcube-router`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Router replicas from values\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.replicas: 3`\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `3`\n\n#### Scenario: Router image from values\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has custom router image\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** container image SHALL be `{{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Router environment variables\n- **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **WHEN** container env is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from fieldRef `metadata.namespace`\n  - `REDIS_ADDR` from `{{ .Values.redis.addr }}`\n  - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from Secret `{{ .Release.Name }}-redis` key `password`\n  - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL: \"http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Router extraEnv injection\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.extraEnv` entries\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** extraEnv entries SHALL be injected into container env\n\n#### Scenario: Router args\n- **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **WHEN** container args are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `--port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n  - `--debug`\n\n#### Scenario: Router liveness probe\n- **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **WHEN** livenessProbe is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `httpGet.path: /health/live`\n  - `httpGet.port: http`\n  - `initialDelaySeconds: 1`\n  - `periodSeconds: 2`\n\n#### Scenario: Router readiness probe\n- **GIVEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **WHEN** readinessProbe is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `httpGet.path: /health/ready`\n  - `httpGet.port: http`\n  - `initialDelaySeconds: 1`\n  - `periodSeconds: 2`\n\n#### Scenario: Router service account conditional\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.serviceAccountName: \"custom-sa\"`\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** `serviceAccountName` SHALL be `custom-sa`\n\n#### Scenario: Router service account empty\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"`\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** `serviceAccountName` SHALL NOT be set (use default)\n\n#### Scenario: Router Service\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** Router Service is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `name: agentcube-router`\n  - `type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}`\n  - `port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}`\n  - `targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n  - Selector: `app: agentcube-router`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-030.5: Workload Manager RBAC\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Workload Manager RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding) with correct permissions.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager ServiceAccount\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** Workload Manager ServiceAccount is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - Labels: `app.kubernetes.io/name: workloadmanager`, `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole sandbox permissions\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]`, `resources: [\"sandboxes\"]`, `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole extension resources\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"sandboxclaims\", \"sandboxtemplates\", \"sandboxwarmpools\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole warm pool status\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"sandboxwarmpools/status\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole CodeInterpreter permissions\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include rules for:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/status\"]`, `verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"codeinterpreters/finalizers\"]`, `verbs: [\"update\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole AgentRuntime permissions\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"update\", \"patch\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole pod permissions\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"pods\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole token review\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"authentication.k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"tokenreviews\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"create\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole secret permissions\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - Subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: workloadmanager`, `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - RoleRef: `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: workloadmanager`, `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-030.6: Router RBAC (Optional)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement optional Router RBAC resources controlled by `router.rbac.create` flag.\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC disabled by default\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.rbac.create: false`\n- **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n- **THEN** Router RBAC resources SHALL NOT be created\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC enabled\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `router.rbac.create: true`\n- **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n- **THEN** Router ServiceAccount, Role, and RoleBinding SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount name\n- **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n- **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n- **THEN** name SHALL be `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Router Role secret permissions\n- **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n- **WHEN** Role rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Router RoleBinding\n- **GIVEN** Router RBAC is enabled\n- **WHEN** RoleBinding is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL reference:\n  - Subject: ServiceAccount with default name\n  - RoleRef: Role with same name\n\n---\n\n### REQ-030.7: Volcano Agent Scheduler (Optional)\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement optional Volcano Agent Scheduler resources controlled by `volcano.scheduler.enabled` flag.\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler disabled by default\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false`\n- **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n- **THEN** Volcano Scheduler resources SHALL NOT be created\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler enabled\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n- **WHEN** helm template is rendered\n- **THEN** ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, and Deployment SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ServiceAccount\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** ServiceAccount is created\n- **THEN** name SHALL be `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ConfigMap\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** ConfigMap is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include `agent-scheduler.conf` with:\n  - `actions: \"allocate\"`\n  - `tiers:` with `plugins: \"predicates,nodeorder\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole CRD permissions\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole pod permissions\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include comprehensive pod permissions:\n  - `pods`, `pods/status`, `pods/binding`, `pods/disruptionbudgets`\n  - `persistentvolumeclaims`, `persistentvolumes`\n  - `nodes`, `namespaces`, `services`, `replicationcontrollers`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole scheduling permissions\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"priorityclasses\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]`\n  - `apiGroups: [\"scheduling.incubator.k8s.io\", \"scheduling.volcano.sh\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"podgroups\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\", \"update\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole storage permissions\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"storage.k8s.io\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"storageclasses\", \"csinodes\", \"csidrivers\", \"csistoragecapacities\", \"volumeattachments\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"list\", \"watch\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRole configmap permissions\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole rules are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"configmaps\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"delete\", \"update\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler ClusterRoleBinding\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler-role`\n  - Subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n  - RoleRef: `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Service\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** Service is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `name: volcano-agent-scheduler-service`\n  - `port: 8080`, `targetPort: 8080`, `name: metrics`\n  - Annotations: `prometheus.io/scrape: \"true\"`, `prometheus.io/port: \"8080\"`\n  - Selector: `app: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Deployment args\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** container args SHALL include:\n  - `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`\n  - `--config=/config/agent-scheduler.conf`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler Deployment volumes\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** it SHALL include volumes:\n  - `name: config`, `configMap.name: volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap`\n  - `name: empty`, `emptyDir: {}`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler security context\n- **GIVEN** Volcano Scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** container securityContext SHALL include:\n  - `runAsNonRoot: true`\n  - `runAsUser: 1000`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano Scheduler replicas from values\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `volcano.scheduler.replicas: 2`\n- **WHEN** Deployment is rendered\n- **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `2`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-030.8: Redis Secret Template\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement Redis Secret template to store Redis password.\n\n#### Scenario: Redis Secret creation\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** Redis Secret is created\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `name: {{ .Release.Name }}-redis`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - `type: Opaque`\n\n#### Scenario: Redis Secret data\n- **GIVEN** values.yaml has `redis.password: \"mysecret\"`\n- **WHEN** Secret is rendered\n- **THEN** `stringData.password` SHALL be `\"mysecret\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Redis Secret labels\n- **GIVEN** helm template is rendered\n- **WHEN** Secret labels are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/name: redis`\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-030.9: CRD Files\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL include CRD files for agentruntimes and codeinterpreters.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD existence\n- **GIVEN** the chart is installed\n- **WHEN** CRDs are applied\n- **THEN** `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD group and version\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CRD is applied\n- **WHEN** CRD spec is validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `spec.group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n  - `spec.versions[0].name: v1alpha1`\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD existence\n- **GIVEN** the chart is installed\n- **WHEN** CRDs are applied\n- **THEN** `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` SHALL be created\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD group and version\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreter CRD is applied\n- **WHEN** CRD spec is validated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `spec.group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n  - `spec.versions[0].name: v1alpha1`\n\n#### Scenario: CRD installation order\n- **GIVEN** helm install is run\n- **WHEN** chart is installed\n- **THEN** CRDs SHALL be installed before other resources\n\n---\n\n### REQ-030.10: .helmignore\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement .helmignore file to exclude unnecessary files from chart packaging.\n\n#### Scenario: Git files ignored\n- **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n- **WHEN** patterns are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include: `.git/`, `.gitignore`\n\n#### Scenario: Version control files ignored\n- **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n- **WHEN** patterns are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include: `.bzr/`, `.bzrignore`, `.hg/`, `.hgignore`, `.svn/`\n\n#### Scenario: Temporary files ignored\n- **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n- **WHEN** patterns are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include: `*.swp`, `*.bak`, `*.tmp`, `*.orig`, `*~`\n\n#### Scenario: IDE files ignored\n- **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n- **WHEN** patterns are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include: `.project`, `.idea/`, `*.tmproj`, `.vscode/`\n\n#### Scenario: Test files ignored\n- **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n- **WHEN** patterns are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include: `tests/`\n\n#### Scenario: Documentation files ignored\n- **GIVEN** .helmignore is created\n- **WHEN** patterns are defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include: `*.md` but NOT `!README.md`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-030.11: Helm Lint and Template Validation\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL pass `helm lint` without errors and `helm template` shall generate valid YAML.\n\n#### Scenario: Helm lint passes\n- **GIVEN** chart structure is complete\n- **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is run\n- **THEN** it SHALL return no errors\n\n#### Scenario: Helm template generates valid YAML\n- **GIVEN** chart structure is complete\n- **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is run\n- **THEN** output SHALL be valid YAML that can be parsed\n\n#### Scenario: Helm template with custom values\n- **GIVEN** custom values file is provided\n- **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base -f custom-values.yaml` is run\n- **THEN** output SHALL reflect custom values overrides\n\n#### Scenario: Helm template with Volcano enabled\n- **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true` is passed\n- **WHEN** `helm template` is run\n- **THEN** output SHALL include Volcano Scheduler resources\n\n#### Scenario: Helm template with Router RBAC enabled\n- **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true` is passed\n- **WHEN** `helm template` is run\n- **THEN** output SHALL include Router RBAC resources\n\n---\n\n### REQ-030.12: Multi-Environment Support\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL support multi-environment deployment through values overrides.\n\n#### Scenario: Development environment values\n- **GIVEN** development values file is provided\n- **WHEN** helm install is run with `-f values-dev.yaml`\n- **THEN** all components SHALL use development-appropriate settings (e.g., lower resources)\n\n#### Scenario: Production environment values\n- **GIVEN** production values file is provided\n- **WHEN** helm install is run with `-f values-prod.yaml`\n- **THEN** all components SHALL use production-appropriate settings (e.g., higher replicas, resources)\n\n#### Scenario: Region-specific Redis configuration\n- **GIVEN** different regions have different Redis addresses\n- **WHEN** helm install is run with `--set redis.addr=redis-region1.svc:6379`\n- **THEN** components SHALL connect to specified Redis address\n\n#### Scenario: Custom image repository override\n- **GIVEN** organization uses private registry\n- **WHEN** helm install is run with `--set router.image.repository=myregistry.com/router`\n- **THEN** Router SHALL use custom image repository\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```yaml\n# values.yaml structure\nvalues:\n  imagePullSecrets: []\n  nameOverride: \"\"\n  fullnameOverride: \"\"\n  \n  redis:\n    addr: string       # Required: Redis address\n    password: string   # Optional: Redis password\n  \n  router:\n    replicas: int\n    image:\n      repository: string\n      pullPolicy: string\n      tag: string\n    service:\n      type: string\n      port: int\n      targetPort: int\n    resources:\n      limits:\n        cpu: string\n        memory: string\n      requests:\n        cpu: string\n        memory: string\n    config: object\n    extraEnv: []\n    serviceAccountName: string\n    rbac:\n      create: bool\n  \n  workloadmanager:\n    replicas: int\n    image:\n      repository: string\n      pullPolicy: string\n      tag: string\n    service:\n      type: string\n      port: int\n    resources:\n      limits:\n        cpu: string\n        memory: string\n      requests:\n        cpu: string\n        memory: string\n    extraEnv: []\n  \n  volcano:\n    scheduler:\n      enabled: bool\n      replicas: int\n      image:\n        repository: string\n        pullPolicy: string\n        tag: string\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml\n├── values.yaml\n├── .helmignore\n├── crds/\n│   ├── agentruntime.yaml\n│   └── codeinterpreter.yaml\n└── templates/\n    ├── _helpers.tpl\n    ├── redis-secret.yaml\n    ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n    ├── agentcube-router.yaml\n    ├── rbac/\n    │   └── workloadmanager.yaml\n    ├── rbac-router.yaml\n    └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml\n```\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Component | Description | Source |\n|----------|-----------|-------------|--------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | All | Namespace from downward API | fieldRef |\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis address | values.redis.addr |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Router, WorkloadManager | Redis password | Secret |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager URL | Constructed from values |\n\n---\n\n## Error Codes\n\n| Error | Exit Code | Message |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| Chart validation failure | 1 | `helm lint` failed: {detail} |\n| Template render failure | 1 | `helm template` failed: {detail} |\n| CRD installation failure | 1 | Failed to install CRD: {detail} |\n| Redis address not provided | 1 | `redis.addr` is required in values |\n| Invalid YAML syntax | 1 | YAML parse error in {file}: {detail} |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| Helm | ≥3.0 | Chart packaging and deployment |\n| Kubernetes | ≥1.21 | API compatibility |\n| Redis | Any | External dependency (session storage) |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` — Chart metadata with correct apiVersion, name, version\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` — Complete configuration tree for all components\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` — Deployment + Service with correct env/probes\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` — Deployment + Service with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` — ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` — Conditional Router RBAC\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` — Conditional Volcano Scheduler\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/templates/redis-secret.yaml` — Redis password Secret\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml` — AgentRuntime CRD (existing, verify completeness)\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter.yaml` — CodeInterpreter CRD (new)\n- [ ] `manifests/charts/base/.helmignore` — Ignore patterns for packaging\n- [ ] `helm lint` passes without errors\n- [ ] `helm template` generates valid YAML\n- [ ] `helm install` succeeds in Kind cluster\n- [ ] Optional components render correctly when enabled/disabled\n- [ ] Values overrides work correctly for multi-environment support\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should the chart support external Redis Operator integration?\n2. Should monitoring and logging configurations be integrated into the chart?\n3. Should multi-cluster deployment be supported through values configuration?\n4. Should the chart include default values for development/testing environments?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml\">\nERROR [126:48] Nested mappings are not allowed in compact mappings\nERROR [138:48] Nested mappings are not allowed in compact mappings\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml":[{"range":{"start":{"line":125,"character":47},"end":{"line":125,"character":85}},"message":"Nested mappings are not allowed in compact mappings","severity":1,"code":0,"source":"YAML"},{"range":{"start":{"line":137,"character":47},"end":{"line":137,"character":77}},"message":"Nested mappings are not allowed in compact mappings","severity":1,"code":0,"source":"YAML"}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/manifests/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775878846568,"end":1775878846580}}}}
